Note that the setting or R_LIBS_SITE in R_HOME/etc/Renviron (and
/etc/R/Renvrion as a convenience symlink) is meant to be a _sensible default
value_ for most situations, not an iron-clad default.  You are free to define
/org/R/library as a first value of what gets into .libPaths() via R_LIBS_SITE
and/or R_LIBS_USER. 

Your systems, your rules. We aim to provide sensible defaults, not to dictate
behaviour. 

Note that the first value shown by .libPaths() in R becomes the default for
install.packages() et al, which can also be overriden on each call (and
likewise for R CMD INSTALL).

