It's less bad than one may think at first -- 'first one found' usually
wins. So you 

      foo_1.2-4 in /usr/local/lib/R/site-library

wins over

      foo_1.2-3 in /usr/lib/R/site-library

by virtue of being first in the $PATH (cf .libPaths() in R).

